<HEADLINE>
1st lead: Syria to withdraw all forces from Lebanon by April 30
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
DAMASCUS, April 3 (Xinhua)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UN envoy Terje Roed-Larsen said 
Sunday that the Syrian government has pledged to remove all Syrian 
troops and intelligence agents from Lebanon by April 30.
</P>
<P>
Larsen made the statement at a joint news conference with Syrian
Foreign Minister Farouq al-Shara after talks with President Bashar 
al-Assad.
</P>
<P>
"All Syrian troops as well as the intelligence apparatus will be
completely withdrawn by April 30," said Larsen.
</P>
<P>
Larsen, UN special envoy for the implementation of UN Resolution
1559 which demands Syria to quit Lebanon, will also hold talks with
senior Lebanese officials in Beirut on the withdrawal timetable on 
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Under mounting pressures from the international community and 
Lebanese opposition, Syria has carried out the first stage of a 
two-phase withdrawal plan, with nearly 4,000 troops out of 14,000 
pulled out of Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
UN Secretary General Kofi Annan as well as Lebanese opposition 
leaders have called upon Syria to complete withdrawal before 
Lebanon's parliamentary elections in May.
</P>
